Preheat your #oven{} to 200°C and pop a large #saucepan{} of water with a generous
pinch of @salt{pinch} on to boil for the pasta. Remove the root and tough dark
green leaves from the @leek{1}. Cut it in half lengthways and then thinly slice.
Chop the @broccoli{1/2} into florets (like small trees).

Add the @penne pasta{200%g} to the pan of boiling water. When the wheat penne
has been cooking for ~{6%minutes}, add the broccoli to the pan, bring back to
the boil and cook for another ~{4%minutes}. Once the wheat pasta and broccoli
are cooked, drain in a #colander{}, pop them back into the pan off the heat and
stir in half of the @creme fraiche{150%g}. Season with a good pinch of salt
and a generous grind of @ground black pepper{}. Keep to one side.

While your wheat pasta cooks, heat a splash of @oil{} in another large saucepan
over medium heat. When hot, add the chopped leeks and cook until soft,
~{4-5%minutes}. Stir occasionally.

Season the leek generously with black pepper then stir in the remaining crème
fraîche. Add the @vegetable stock powder{1/2} and @water{50%ml} and stir to
dissolve the stock powder. Add the @smoked fish mix{215%g} and stir gently to
make sure all the fish is coated in the sauce.

Transfer the creamy fish mix to an #ovenproof dish{}. Spread the wheat pasta
and broccoli on top, sprinkle on the @grated hard Italian style cheese{40%g}
and bake for ~{15%minutes}.

> TIP: If it looks like your pasta is becoming too brown, simply cover it with
> foil for the last 5 mins.

> IMPORTANT: The fish is cooked when opaque in the centre.

Once your fish wheat pasta bake is golden on top remove it from the oven and
leave it to sit for a minute or two. Spoon into #bowls{}. Enjoy!